StatementHelp.#cdata:
Opens, manages, or closes the LISTING destination. 

Syntax: 
(1) ODS LISTING <action>;  
(2) ODS LISTING <DATAPANEL=number | DATA | PAGE > <FILE=file-specification>;

Produces a SAS data set from an output object and manages the selection and exclusion lists 
for the OUTPUT destination. 

Syntax:
(1) ODS OUTPUT action;  
(2) ODS OUTPUT data-set-definition(s);

Opens, manages, or closes the specified destination (PRINTER, PS, PCL, PDF), which produces
printable output.

Syntax: 
(1) ODS PRINTER|PS|PCL|PDF <(<ID=>identifier)> <action>;  
(2) ODS PRINTER|PS|PCL|PDF <(<ID=>identifier)> <option(s)>;

Syntax: ODS VERIFY <ON | OFF | ERROR | WARN>; 

Prints or suppresses a message indicating that a style definition or a table definition being 
used is not supplied by SAS.

Opens, manages, or closes the RTF destination, which produces measured output that 
is written in Rich Text Format for use with Microsoft Word 2002.

Syntax: 
ODS RTF <(<ID=> identifier)> action;  
ODS RTF <(<ID=> identifier)> <option(s)>;

Opens, manages, or closes the RTF destination, which produces measured output that 
is written in Rich Text Format for use with Microsoft Word 2002.

Syntax: 
ODS TAGSETS.RTF <(<ID=> identifier)> action;  
ODS TAGSETS.RTF <(<ID=> identifier)> <option(s)>;

The ODS PACKAGE statement opens, adds to, publishes, or closes one SAS Output Delivery 
System (ODS) package object. 

Syntax: 
(1) ODS PACKAGE (<name>) OPEN <options>;  
(2) ODS PACKAGE (<name>) ADD FILE="file-specification" | DATA=member-specification 
      MIMETYPE="string" <PATH="path-specification"><options>;  
(3) ODS PACKAGE (<name>) PUBLISH transport PROPERTIES(transport-property-1="value-1" ... 
      transport-property-n="value-n");  
(4) ODS PACKAGE (<name>) CLOSE <CLEAR>;

Opens, manages, or closes the specified tagset destination.

Syntax: 
(1) ODS directory.tagset-name file-specification <option(s)>;  
(2) ODS directory.tagset-name file-specification action;

Opens, manages, or closes the EPUB and EPUB2 destinations, which generate EPUB e-books. 

Syntax: 
ODS EPUB <(<ID=> identifier)> < action> ; 
ODS EPUB <(<ID=> identifier)> <option(s)> ; 
ODS EPUB2 <(<ID=> identifier)> < action> ; 
ODS EPUB2 <(<ID=> identifier)> <option(s)> ;

Opens, manages, or closes the EPUB3 destination, which generates EPUB e-books. 

Syntax: 
ODS EPUB3 <(<ID=> identifier)> < action> ; 
ODS EPUB3 <(<ID=> identifier)> <option(s)> ;

Opens, manages, or closes the HTML5 destination, which produces HTML 5.0 output that contains embedded style sheets.

Syntax: 
ODS HTML5 <(<ID=> identifier)> < action> ; 
ODS HTML5 <(<ID=> identifier)> <option(s)> ;

Opens, manages, or closes the ODS destination for PowerPoint, which produces PowerPoint output.

Syntax: 
ODS POWERPOINT <(<ID=> identifier)> < action> ; 
ODS POWERPOINT <(<ID=> identifier)> <option(s)> ;

Opens, manages, or closes the ODS destination for Excel, which produces Excel spreadsheet files 
compatible with Microsoft Office 2010 and later versions.

Syntax: 
ODS EXCEL <(<ID=> identifier)> < action> ; 
ODS EXCEL <(<ID=> identifier)> <option(s)> ;
